sub_title: Forbes Councils Member | Europe 40Under40 Honoree | Business Development Executive | Women in Tech Ambassador & Mentor
summary:
Forbes Councils official Member and thought Leader, Europe 40Under40 Top Business Leader, Forbes Fellow under 30, Women in Tech Ambassador and Mentor, Member of the Financial Times group “Women at the Top”, Techstars Startup Mentor, Member of the MACH Alliance, Business mentor.

Experienced C-level executive and corporate Board Member with a demonstrated history of 15 years working in business development, international affairs and IT industry. Cross-functional energetic leader, scaling high-performing sales functions within a hyper-growth software business- enterprise integrations, web and mobile development, software as a service (SaaS) to Fortune 1000 companies.

Skilled manager with strong business acumen in international B2B sales- responsible for all phases of the sales cycle, from planning and pre-sales, to negotiating, closing contracts, customer success and accelerating growth, while building strong relationships with customers, strategic corporate management, multiple project coordination, budget planning, and more.

awards:
[{'title': 'Forbes Fellow - Program Under 30, Boston, USA 2018', 'description': "Hello Ivana and congratulations, 
We are pleased to announce that you have been accepted into the Forbes Fellows program and have been selected out of thousands of applicants. With this invitation you'll be granted access to an incredible community at our Under 30 Summit in Boston from September 30th 2018.
We’re excited to have you join as a Fellow!

Best, 
Steven Bertoni
Vice President & Senior Editor Forbes Under 30", 'issuer': 'Forbes Under 30', 'date': {'month': 9, 'day': None, 'year': 2018}}, {'title': 'Keynote speaker at Interaction 2017: Direct Marketing to a Global Audience, Akron, Ohio, USA', 'description': 'On Friday, May 19, 2017, the University of Akron’s Gary L. and Karen S. Taylor Institute for Direct Marketing hosted its annual thought leadership event, Interaction. Interaction 2017 featured the theme of Direct Marketing to a Global Audience. With current technology, including the well-documented prevalence of mobile devices, the world is becoming smaller.
Keynote speakers:
- Karen Haefling, VP of Marketing, The Vitamix Corporation
- Dr. Andrew Thomas, Professor, International Business, The University of Akron
- Ivana Nikolik, Deputy CEO, Agency for Foreign Investments & Export Promotion of the R. Macedonia

Source: 
https://www.uakron.edu/cba/centers-and-institutes/taylor/professionals/interaction/2017/', 'issuer': 'The University of Akron, College of Business', 'date': {'month': 5, 'day': None, 'year': 2017}}, {'title': 'Award "International Best Practice in Investment Promotion", Tucson, Arizona, USA', 'description': 'The Site Selectors Guild, the world’s largest group of senior site location advisors, honored Invest Macedonia with the 2017 International Best Practice in Investment Promotion Award at its annual conference, March 15, 2017.
https://siteselectorsguild.com/news/2017-international-best-practice-in-investment-promotion-award-invest-macedonia/

SSG members nominate Investment Promotion Agencies (IPAs) from around the world for the International Best Practice Award. Invest Macedonia was honored this year with this prestigious award for their work attracting and developing foreign investment and cooperation with site selection consultants. The CEO of Invest Macedonia, Ms. Ivana Nikolik attended as a keynote speaker and was honored to receive the Award. 
As chairman of the SSG International Committee, Roel Spee presented Invest Macedonia with the award:
“Invest Macedonia has done excellent work in the international space,” said Spee. “Especially for a country of its size, with a population of just over 2 million, they are truly excelling. We are proud to honor them with this award.”

Source: https://siteselectorsguild.com/news/2017-international-best-practice-in-investment-promotion-award-invest-macedonia/', 'issuer': 'Site Selectors Guild', 'date': {'month': 3, 'day': None, 'year': 2017}}, {'title': 'Keynote speaker at international conference "Empowering Women trough access to land" Tirana, Albania', 'description': 'On 10 March the conference “Empowering Women through Access to Land” will take place in Tirana, Albania, jointly organized by GIZ and FAO, in cooperation with the International Union of Notaries. The conference will be organized into three panels. In each of the panel representatives of ministries, registration offices, notaries, equality bodies and NGOs from the region and international organizations will discuss on the importance of having the property registered, challenges, and success stories of gender equitable land management. Solutions and ways forward on how to improve women registration in land ownership will be discussed.
The conference will be preceded by a pre-conference workshop on 9 March. This will consist of a technical workshop during which participants from Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Kosovo, Macedonia, Montenegro and Serbia will reach a commitment concerning the steps necessary to implement the priority recommendations that emerged from the Legal Assessment Tools and SDG indicator 5.a.2 assessments, and will exchange ideas on good practices and lessons learned.

Source: https://gender-works.giz.de/events2017/empowering-women-through-access-to-land/', 'issuer': 'GIZ (Deutsche Gesellschaft für Internationale Zusammenarbeit) and UN FAO', 'date': {'month': 3, 'day': None, 'year': 2017}}, {'title': 'Keynote speaker and organizer of the Macedonia Manufacturing Expo-USAID 2016 conference', 'description': 'Macedonia Manufacturing Expo 2016 organized with USAID is the first business-to-business conference in Macedonia that is bringing together domestic and international companies from the light manufacturing industry in search of new partnerships. We invited some of the organizers and keynote speakers to tell us more about the challenges facing the Macedonian light manufacturing industry. One of them was Ms. Ivana Nikolik, the Deputy CEO at the Agency for Foreign Investments and Export Promotion of the Republic of Macedonia.

Source: https://www.facebook.com/USAIDNorthMacedonia/videos/macedonia-manufacturing-expo-2016-industry-challenges/1089560311120729/', 'issuer': 'Macedonia Manufacturing Expo-USAID', 'date': {'month': 9, 'day': None, 'year': 2016}}, {'title': 'Keynote speaker at IBF -International Business Forum by MUSIAD, Skopje 2016', 'description': 'IBF (International Business Forum) is an international platform established by MUSIAD in 1995, with the participation of businessmen from the business world of 66 countries, and the annual congress and accompanying commercial activities. 

Independent Industrialists’ and Businessmen’s Association MUSIAD from Turkey organized on 21 October 2016 in Skopje the Balkans Business Forum gathering companies from the construction, tourism, agriculture and food processing, textile sector and metallurgy. 
The Deputy CEO of the Agency for Foreign Investments and Export Promotion of the Republic of Macedonia, Ivana Nikolik had a presentation on investment potentials of Macedonia on that occasion.
She informed potential Turkish investors on macroeconomic indicators in Macedonia, improving the business climate, competitive advantages that Macedonia offers to foreign investors and attractive sectors for investing, such as metal-processing and electrical sector, the sector of auto parts, etc. It was pointed out on this occasion the progress of Macedonia according to Doing Business Report of the World Bank 2016 placing Macedonia at the 10th ahead of all countries in the region. Turkish investors were then familiarized with the growth of economic indicators and undertaking ongoing reforms for the EU accession. 

Among the speakers at the IBF Forum were representatives of Turkey, Macedonia, Serbia, Montenegro, Romania, Albania, Bosnia and Hercegovina, Kosovo.

Source: https://www.musiad.org.tr/icerik/uluslararasi-is-forumu-ibf-124', 'issuer': 'MUSIAD Balkan Business Forum', 'date': {'month': 9, 'day': None, 'year': 2016}}]
